    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That \"balance\" sounds pretty idealistic. But if the risks include things like xenophobia or full-scale war, isn't it more accurate to say that the ideology itself is fundamentally flawed? How can you say the benefits \"often outweigh\" something as destructive as war?",
